Here is a simple JavaScript program that generates and prints out the ASCII character and hexadecimal codes for 0 to 7F:

```javascript
// Function to convert a character to its ASCII code
function charToAsciiCode(char) {
  return char.charCodeAt(0);
}

// Function to convert an ASCII code to its corresponding character
function asciiCodeToChar(code) {
  return String.fromCharCode(code);
}

// Loop through the range of characters (0 to 7F)
for (let i = 0; i <= 127; i++) {
  const char = asciiCodeToChar(i);
  console.log(`Character: ${char} | ASCII Code: ${i} | Hexadecimal Code: ${i.toString(16)}`);
}
```

This program defines two functions, `charToAsciiCode` and `asciiCodeToChar`, which convert a character to its ASCII code and an ASCII code to its corresponding character, respectively. Then, it loops through the range of characters from 0 to 7F (inclusive), printing out each character's ASCII code and hexadecimal representation.
